
--CURDIR--/reg_issue2559.fz:24:10: error 1: IMPLEMENTATION RESTRICTION: An expression used as a lazy value must not contain feature declarations
say (0 : (match true { a true_ => { say a; nil }; b false_ => { say b; nil } }))
---------^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Declared features:
declared 'a' at --CURDIR--/reg_issue2559.fz:24:24:
say (0 : (match true { a true_ => { say a; nil }; b false_ => { say b; nil } }))
-----------------------^
declared 'b' at --CURDIR--/reg_issue2559.fz:24:51:
say (0 : (match true { a true_ => { say a; nil }; b false_ => { say b; nil } }))
--------------------------------------------------^
This is an implementation restriction that should be removed in a future version of Fuzion.

To solve this, create a helper feature 'lazy_value' that calculates the value as follows:

  lazy_value => '(match true { a true_ => { say a; nil }; b false_ => { say b; nil } })'

and then use 'lazy_value' as instead of the original expression.

one error.
